00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:50,580
And with giving you that spiritual gift,

1005
00:50:50,580 --> 00:50:55,580
he has the expectation that you would be a good steward

1006
00:50:56,220 --> 00:50:58,260
of what he has given to you

1007
00:50:58,260 --> 00:51:00,740
and that you would use your spiritual gift

1008
00:51:00,740 --> 00:51:05,020
to bring honor and glory to him and to profit the body.

1009
00:51:06,740 --> 00:51:09,380
And by the way, it's okay for God

1010
00:51:09,380 --> 00:51:10,940
to have that expectation of us

1011
00:51:10,940 --> 00:51:13,460
because he's the one that gave us the gift.

1012
00:51:14,600 --> 00:51:15,520
Amen?

1013
00:51:15,520 --> 00:51:18,860
He gave it to us and then he expects

1014
00:51:18,860 --> 00:51:22,960
that we would use it for his honor and for his glory.

1015
00:51:22,960 --> 00:51:25,500
You ever hear about Moses?

1016
00:51:26,320 --> 00:51:28,020
Of course, Moses, a household name.

1017
00:51:28,900 --> 00:51:33,900
Bezalel, Holyab, not as well known.

1018
00:51:35,660 --> 00:51:37,480
But you know who those men are?

1019
00:51:37,480 --> 00:51:39,620
Those are the men that God equipped

1020
00:51:39,620 --> 00:51:42,860
to do the work for the tabernacle.

1021
00:51:42,860 --> 00:51:45,840
Moses was the one that was given the blueprints,

1022
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:47,580
if you will.

1023
00:51:47,580 --> 00:51:51,100
But God says to Moses, I've equipped these men,

1024
00:51:51,100 --> 00:51:54,540
not only to do, but then also to teach others.

1025
00:51:54,540 --> 00:51:56,860
And you know what God expected of Bezalel?

1026
00:51:56,860 --> 00:51:59,060
He expected that he would do the work

1027
00:51:59,060 --> 00:52:00,760
that he equipped him to do.

1028
00:52:01,860 --> 00:52:04,300
God's equipped us this morning.

1029
00:52:04,300 --> 00:52:05,420
And I just wonder today,

1030
00:52:05,420 --> 00:52:08,500
as I look at this passage of scripture

1031
00:52:08,500 --> 00:52:12,820
in 2 Timothy 4, and I read those words

1032
00:52:12,820 --> 00:52:17,820
that he is profitable to me for the ministry.

1033
00:52:18,780 --> 00:52:20,600
Of course, this morning is not the first time

1034
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:22,320
I ever read these words.

1035
00:52:23,080 --> 00:52:26,280
I do remember, not the day or the time,

1036
00:52:26,280 --> 00:52:29,180
but I remember the first time I ever read these words.

1037
00:52:30,280 --> 00:52:32,200
And I remember reading these words

1038
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,220
and asking myself this question.

1039
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:38,920
Would it be said of me that I'm profitable

1040
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:39,860
for the ministry?

1041
00:52:41,040 --> 00:52:42,360
I've been saved for 27 years.

1042
00:52:42,360 --> 00:52:44,580
It was probably 25, 26 years ago

1043
00:52:44,580 --> 00:52:46,720
that I read those words for the first time.

1044
00:52:47,880 --> 00:52:50,040
And God used those words to grip my heart.

1045
00:52:51,040 --> 00:52:54,280
And I had to answer that question honestly and humbly.

1046
00:52:54,280 --> 00:52:56,280
Would I be profitable for the ministry?

1047
00:52:56,280 --> 00:53:01,280
If my pastor was writing,

1048
00:53:01,780 --> 00:53:03,800
would he say, bring him because he's profitable

1049
00:53:03,800 --> 00:53:05,120
to me for the ministry?

1050
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:09,640
And I desire that for myself,

1051
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:11,760
and I hope that you would desire for yourself

1052
00:53:11,760 --> 00:53:13,920
this morning as well,

1053
00:53:13,920 --> 00:53:16,580
that God would say of each of us

1054
00:53:16,580 --> 00:53:20,320
that we are profitable for the ministry,

1055
00:53:20,320 --> 00:53:22,940
that we're fulfilling the work

1056
00:53:22,940 --> 00:53:25,820
that God has equipped us to do,

1057
00:53:25,820 --> 00:53:27,340
that we're not negligent,

1058
00:53:27,340 --> 00:53:30,420
that we're not MIA, right?

1059
00:53:30,420 --> 00:53:31,260
No, no, no.

1060
00:53:31,260 --> 00:53:33,060
We're doing what God has called us to do.

1061
00:53:33,060 --> 00:53:34,720
And you say, but it's only, no, no, no.

1062
00:53:34,720 --> 00:53:36,260
It's not, but it's only.

1063
00:53:36,260 --> 00:53:37,780
If God equipped you for it,

1064
00:53:37,780 --> 00:53:39,700
it's the most important thing.

1065
00:53:39,700 --> 00:53:43,260
And by the way, the only thing that you're accountable for

1066
00:53:43,260 --> 00:53:45,640
is to do what God equipped you to do.

1067
00:53:45,640 --> 00:53:46,520
So we come to the place and say,

1068
00:53:46,520 --> 00:53:48,600
God, I understand the ministry.

1069
00:53:48,600 --> 00:53:50,040
We've defined it.

1070
00:53:50,040 --> 00:53:51,960
God, I wanna discover my place in the ministry.

1071
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:54,960
God, I want you to use me for your honor and for your glory.

1072
00:53:54,960 --> 00:53:56,140
Thank you for enabling me.

1073
00:53:56,140 --> 00:53:57,240
Thank you for equipping me.

1074
00:53:57,240 --> 00:54:00,440
Now use me in your work.

1075
00:54:00,440 --> 00:54:02,500
What a joy it is to be used of God.

1076
00:54:02,500 --> 00:54:03,340
Let's pray.

1077
00:54:03,340 --> 00:54:04,400
Father, we love you.

1078
00:54:04,400 --> 00:54:06,340
How we thank you for loving us.

1079
00:54:07,720 --> 00:54:10,140
Thank you for using us.

1080
00:54:10,140 --> 00:54:11,660
We thank you for saving us,

1081
00:54:11,660 --> 00:54:14,880
and we understand that you saved us to service.

1082
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:16,780
And Lord, I pray that as we,

1083
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:21,800
this morning would rejoice in our salvation,

1084
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:23,600
that we'd also rejoice in the fact

1085
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:25,280
that we are your workmanship,

1086
00:54:26,240 --> 00:54:27,680
that you saved us to serve.

1087
00:54:27,680 --> 00:54:30,380
And Lord, I pray you help us to discover

1088
00:54:30,380 --> 00:54:31,600
our place in the ministry.

1089
00:54:31,600 --> 00:54:34,800
I pray that we'd evaluate our hearts and our own lives

1090
00:54:34,800 --> 00:54:36,480
here in this moment of invitation

1091
00:54:37,720 --> 00:54:40,080
to contemplate that question

1092
00:54:40,080 --> 00:54:43,600
of whether or not it would be said of us as individuals

1093
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:46,440
that we're profitable for the ministry.

1094
00:54:47,400 --> 00:54:50,360
I pray the Holy Spirit of God would have his will and way.

1095
00:54:51,440 --> 00:54:55,180
Decisions would be made that would please you, Lord.

1096
00:54:55,180 --> 00:54:56,760
We'll thank you for the work that you'll do.

1097
00:54:56,760 --> 00:54:58,120
For it's in Christ's name we pray.

1098
00:54:58,120 --> 00:54:59,320
We just stand with you.

